Sirens can be opened by right-clicking on them then you can insert a siren track which can be made using the template folder. When a siren get powered by redstone the sound will either play once or will loop depending on the category. The sound will play with a radius equal to the volume of the selected track.

You can disable or lower their sound using the noteblock volume slider.

Here are some tracks I recommend for griefing:

- AMS siren (god awful but low range)

- Beep siren (high pitched)

- Missile silo (very loud and good range)

- Air raid (one of the best)

- EAS screech
